placement_text: AdDoors along the corridor should provide a clear opening of at least 850 mm measured from the face of the open door to the doorstop (AS 1428.1‑2009). Provide at least 1000 mm corridor width for an accessible path of travel and ensure sliding doors have a minimum 60 mm clearance. Door handles or controls should be positioned between 900‑1100 mm above the floor and doors with closers must be operable with a maximum force of 20 N.d text

Add Accessible bathroom: Provide a circulation space of around 2000 mm x 1600 mm to allow wheelchair turning. Door should swing outward or be sliding so it does not obstruct the circulation area and it should provide a clear opening of at least 850 mm with a flush threshold. Install grab rails around the WC and in the shower, with a fold-down shower seat, and leave at least 800 mm clear space beside the toilet for side transfer. Use slip‑resistant flooring and lever tap fixtures.text
Accessible entry: provide continuous path of travel at least 1000 mm wide with no steps. Include ramp for level change.
